              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of βραχίων ‘arm,’ not occurring in the NT) power as an expression of the activity of a person or supernatural being{N:001}</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>power</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In some languages there is no abstract term for ‘power.’ The equivalent of doing something by the power of someone is ‘someone makes it possible to do’ or, in a figurative sense, ‘someone gives strength to do.’</Comments>
